title: The Break-In
description: T.J. gets detention during recess. His friends must enlist the help of the rest of the playground to rescue him.

title: The New Kid
description: A new kid comes to 3rd Street School. He, as all new kids are, is only referred to as "New Kid". Can he get his name back?

title: Parents' Night
description: Parents Night comes to Third Street School and all the kids are excited...except Spinelli. When she says her parents can't come, the gang realizes that none of them has ever seen Mr. or Mrs. Spinelli.

title: Swing on Thru to the Other Side
First Name, Ashley
description: The title becomes an embarrassing revelation about Spinelli.

title: King Gus
description: Gus is appointed the new temporary king when King Bob has to leave for a week to have his tonsils taken out.

title: Big Brother Chad
description: Vince's big brother Chad is coming to pick him up after school. All the other kids reminisce about how cool he was. But how cool is he, really?

title: My Fair Gretchen
description: Gretchen has been selected for placement in a school for the gifted, and her friends try to change her, hoping the school will turn her down.

title: Speedy, We Hardly Knew Ye
description: A beloved hamster in Miss Grotke's class dies, leading generations of students and somehow former students to 3rd Street School to mourn his passing.

title: I Will Kick No More Forever
The Pest
description: A boy named Jeffery admits to harboring an enormous crush on Gretchen, and insists that she should be his girlfriend.

title: The Box
description: Finster creates 'the box' as a new punishment for kids and puts T.J. in it to try out its effects.

title: The Trial
description: Spinelli is put on trial for hitting Randall with a rock during a dirt clod war; and though she proclaims her innocence, she refuses to take the stand in her defense.

title: The Great Jungle Gym Stand Off
description: The kids organize a protest when Principal Prickley arranges for the jungle gym, Old Rusty, to be torn down.

title: The Experiment
description: T.J. and his friends hear of a bleak near future where boys and girls like to kiss, and conduct an experiment to determine if there's any truth to it.

title: The Game
description: A game with a bad reputation invades the playground...and one by one, the kids succumb to its strange power.

title: The Lost Ball
description: Gus accidentally kicks a ball over a fence. Can he get it back, or will he forever be known as the kid who lost the best ball the playground ever had?

title: Gretchen and the Secret of Yo
The Girl Was Trouble
description: Gretchen is sent to the principal's office and recalls how a search for her missing hand-held computer turned her into a troublemaker.

title: Copycat Kid
description: After Vince saves Mikey from being hit by a baseball, Mikey notices how cool Vince is and tries to be just like him.

title: Operation Stuart
description: T.J. and his friends try to keep the teachers from finding out about Stuart, the mangy cat living behind the dumpster at school.

title: Pharaoh Bob
description: King Bob makes the kids build a pyramid in his honor.

title: The Hypnotist
description: An entertainer comes to an assembly at school and fails to hypnotize Miss Finster...but does manage to convince Mr. Prickly that he is only 6 years old.

title: Mama's Girl
description: Spinelli gets an onslaught of flak for inadvertently calling Ms. Grotke "Mama."

title: Omega Kids
description: T.J. and his crew find out they have a previously overcrowded 3rd Street School all to themselves.

title: Yes, Mikey, Santa Does Shave: Part 1
Yes, Mikey, Santa Does Shave: Part 2
The Story of Whomps
description: Principal Prickly declares T.J.'s trademark dirty word substitute "whomps" as a dirty word and tries to punish any kid who says it.

title: Weekend at Muriel's
description: Spinelli must try to survive living with Miss Finster when her parents dump her off on Finster for the weekend.

title: The Break-Up
description: A school assignment puts the friendship of T.J. and his crew at risk.

title: Outcast Ashley
description: Ashley A. is thrown out of the Ashley's for committing a major social faux pas. No longer repressing her interest in astronomy, she starts to hang out with Gretchen and gives her fashion advice while they both await the arrival of an upcoming total solar eclipse.

title: Dodgeball City
description: A second grader reveals Gus' past as a terror on the dodgeball court, a fact of his life he thought he could put behind him.

title: A Career to Remember
description: After Career Day at school, all the kids plan out what they're going to do when they grow up except for Spinelli, who can't decide what she wants to do and fears it means she won't have a career.

title: Stand Up Randall
description: Randall finds a joke book and memorizes the jokes to become funny at school, but T.J. seeks revenge after Randall starts making jokes about Mikey being fat.

title: The Shiner
description: T.J. comes to school with a black eye and refuses to say how he got it; leading all the kids to believe he got it doing something heroic, and T.J. revels in the perks of being a hero, until the story grows too much.

title: My Funny Valentines
description: T.J. is vehemently opposed to Valentine's Day. So much so, that when he makes a collection of grotesque and vile anti-Valentine cards for all female pupils at 3rd Street School, they interpret them as unique love notes individually for them... until they realize he sent them to everybody, and vow to make him pay!

title: The First Picture Show
description: T.J. vows to attend the first screening of a movie based on his favorite cartoon character.

title: The Big Prank
description: T.J. is goaded by the other kids into playing the ultimate prank on King Bob before the end of the school day.

title: The Spy Who Came in from the Playground
The Rules
description: A depression-era school rule book is discovered by the kids at the school library.

title: Spinelli's Masterpiece
description: Spinelli make a huge impression with an elaborate chalk drawing on the school playground.

title: Bonky Fever
description: Mikey is about to turn ten years old, and he's scared. So scared, in fact that he reverts to his old childhood fan-dom for Bonky... the kind of show that nobody over the age of five should be into.

title: Prince Randall
description: Randall blackmails King Bob into making him Prince of the Playground.

title: Big Ol' Mikey
description: Mikey begins to fear for his future when Gretchen's hand-held PC Galileo makes a gross miscalculation about his future height.
